.TH wrp_satmask 1 "February 2026" "arma-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
wrp_satmask \- export satellite and mask tiles from modern WRP MapInfo
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wrp_satmask
.RI --db
.I a3db.sqlite
.RI [ --out <dir> ]
.RI [ --dump-tiles ]
.I input.wrp
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wrp_satmask
extracts sat_lco/mask_lco tiles listed in the WRP MapInfo block, mosaics them into PNG canvases, and writes
.B _sat_lco.png
(always) and
.B _mask_lco.png
(modern WRPs only). Legacy WRP v2/v3 files generate only the sat output. Tile assets are resolved through the supplied A3DB database.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "--db " a3db.sqlite
Path to the A3DB SQLite index used to resolve PBO contents. Required.
.TP
.BI "--out " dir
Directory where outputs and diagnostics are written (default: input file directory).
.TP
.B --dump-tiles
Print the extracted tile paths and parsed coordinates.
.TP
.BI "--max-resolution " N
Cap the largest output dimension to N (default: 0 for no cap).
.TP
.B -v
Enable verbose logging.
.TP
.BR -h , " --help"
Show help.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR wrp_heightmap (1)
